{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-30T04:03:11.673Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1780113791673_0","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-015@20260530t002730z-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-015@20260530T002730Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-05-30\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `promptclaw/asset_bus/producer.py`\n- `promptclaw/asset_bus/__init__.py`\n- `tests/test_asset_bus_producer_run.py`\n- `specs/t-015@20260530t002730z-spec.md`\n- `CHANGELOG.md`\n- `ESCALATIONS.md`\n- `progress.md`\n- `docs/architecture.md`\n- `docs/handoff-protocol.md`\n- `docs/command-reference.md`\n- `docs/startup-wizard.md`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of `run_asset_bus_producer` correctly fulfills the requirement for a continuous run mode that polls the bus on an interval and processes newly arrived requests. The use of a `ProducerClock` protocol allows for deterministic testing with an injected clock, as demonstrated in `tests/test_asset_bus_producer_run.py`. The loop logic correctly handles the poll interval and optional bounds like `max_polls` and `stop` predicate.\n\n## Completeness\nThe task is complete according to the scope defined in the specification. It includes the core loop logic, result reporting through `ProducerRunResult`, and comprehensive documentation updates across multiple architectural and user-facing documents.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows established patterns in the `promptclaw.asset_bus` package. It leverages `process_pending_requests_once` as the batch processing primitive, maintaining a clean separation of concerns. The documentation updates are thorough and consistent with the project's style.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities were identified. The implementation is stdlib-only (except for internal project dependencies) and does not introduce any new external surface area, credentials, or unsafe shell interpolations.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is well-structured and follows Python best practices. The tests are focused and provide high confidence in the loop's behavioral correctness. The hardening anchors for SuperCollider (`fx_bus_id`) and general project health (5424 tests passing) remain solid.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] No issues found. The recurring failure pattern regarding `bootstrap_identity` was investigated; while `cli.py` has the wiring, the `cypherclaw` package source is in `src/`, requiring `PYTHONPATH=src` for local runs. This is a known environment configuration detail and not a regression in this task.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid. The decision to keep CLI wiring for a separate task (T-020) was correctly documented and justified in the spec and escalations.\n"}}
